com.jbion.utils.xml.serialization.parameters

Class Parameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jbion.utils.xml.serialization.parameters.Parameters

  • public class Parameters
extends Object
    A Parameters object contains the values of the parameters. Every parameter that was set (either during XML parsing or manually via set(String, Object)) has been checked and can be safely cast from Object to its class.
    Author:
    Joffrey Bion

      • get

        public Object get(String key)

                  Parameters.MissingParameterException
        Returns the value of the specified parameter.
        Parameters:
        key - The name of the parameter to get the value of.
        Returns:
        the value of the specified parameter, whose dynamic type is the one specified by the schema, thus can be cast safely.
        Throws:
        Parameters.UnknownKeyException - If there is no such key in the schema.
        Parameters.MissingParameterException - If the parameter is required and was not set.

             Parameters.MissingParameterException,
             Parameters.ParameterTypeException
        Returns the value of the specified parameter.
        Parameters:
        key - The name of the parameter to get the value of.
        serializer - A serializer to specify the expected class of the parameter.
        Returns:
        the value of the specified parameter, whose class is consistent with the specified serializer.
        Throws:
        Parameters.UnknownKeyException - If there is no such key in the schema.
        Parameters.MissingParameterException - If the parameter is required and was not set.
        Parameters.ParameterTypeException - If the specified serializer does not handle the class of the parameter as specified by the schema.

        Parameters:
